OL,3,CSoldiers from 'distinguished' barracks
OL,4,C'caught wearing Nazi uniforms to party'
OL,6,FAccording to the British Army's
OL,7,Fofficial code of conduct, "Soldiers at
OL,8,Fall levels are held to the highest
OL,9,Fstandards whether they're on or off
OL,10,Fduty.
OL,12,F"If any individual is believed to have
OL,13,Ffailed to meet those standards, we
OL,14,Fwill investigate, and will take
OL,15,Fappropriate action where necessary.
OL,17,F"Any service personnel who are found
OL,18,Fto have committed an offence,
OL,19,Fincluding a criminal offence under the
OL,20,FArmed Forces Act 2006, are dealt with
OL,21,Fthrough the disciplinary process."
